Notes are public in public repos and most tooling ignores refs/notes/*.
Never write secrets to notes: git notes remove does not erase history.
Use gitleaks and hooks.
Run sync-init when a remote exists so notes actually travel.

Local workflow footguns learned the hard way:
- Git hooks inherit git-local env vars. Clear `git rev-parse --local-env-vars` before running nested git-based tests from hooks.
- Avoid split-brain local setups where a canonical-looking path behaves like the git dir while the active checkout is elsewhere. In this repo, prefer jj workspaces over git worktrees for parallel local work.
